The Global Citizen Festival, which began in 2012, is a continuation of the Global Poverty Project, an international advocacy group that hopes to end poverty by increasing the number of people actively struggling against poverty.
In order to get free tickets for the event (unless you want to pay for VIP tickets), concert visitors have to complete a series of tasks or "actions" such as volunteering, emailing world leaders, calling, or other means to help raise awareness of their goal of ending poverty.
